san josé state university has transfer course agreements with over 130 california public colleges and universities. note that not all courses transfer automatically. please view the articulation page for the most current details about transfer credits. submit official transcripts via one of the following three methods: 1) electronic transcripts (preferred method) should be sent to etranscript@sjsu.edu directly from your school(s). 2) send by mail. san jose state university one washington square san josé, ca 95192-0016 3) drop the sealed envelope in the overnight drop box by the student services center(ssc)'s entrance. put attention to the undergraduate admissions office. you will receive a confirmation email once the official transcript is received. the notification will include the approximate time when your transfer credit will appear on your transfer credit report on mysjsu(see below). depending on the time of the year, it usually takes at least 10 business days to process. submit official transcripts via one of the following three methods: 1) electronic transcripts (preferred method) should be sent to etranscript@sjsu.edu directly from your school(s). 2) send by mail. san jose state university one washington square san josé, ca 95192-0009 3) drop the sealed envelope in the overnight drop box by the student services center (ssc)'s entrance. put “attention office of the registrar”. if you have any questions, contact your graduation evaluator directly. please contact gape at graduate@sjsu.edu locate your transfer credit status from your mysjsu portal.   phone: 408-283-7500 (select option 3) fax: 408-924-2077 email: general inquiries: registrar@sjsu.edu docusign forms submission: records-regist@sjsu.edu phone hours: mon - fri: 9:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m. live chat hours: mon - fri: 9:00 a.m. - 10:30 a.m. and 12:30 p.m. - 2:00 p.m. closed weekends and holidays student services center (ssc), window "r" (first floor of north garage, enter on 9th street) hours: mon.- thu: 8:1